        "question_html": "<p><span class=\"english\">Write a paragraph on </span><span class=\"english\">‘Women Empowerment’</span><span class=\"english\"> within 10 sentences.</span><span><span> </span></span><span><span> </span></span><span><span> </span></span><span><span> </span></span><span class=\"english\">10</span><span><span> </span></span><span><span> </span></span><span><span> </span></span><span><span> </span></span></p>",
        "options_html": [],
        "correct_answer_html": null,
        "solution_html": "<p><span class=\"english\">Women Empowerment</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Women empowerment refers to giving women equal rights, opportunities, and freedom in every sphere of life. It ensures that women can access education, healthcare, and employment without discrimination. An empowered woman gains confidence to make her own choices and stand against injustice. Education plays a vital role because it helps women to break the cycle of poverty and ignorance. Economic independence </span><span class=\"english\">allows women to support themselves and contribute to family income. When women actively participate in politics and leadership, society becomes more balanced and democratic. Empowerment also improves health, reduces violence, and promotes equality between men and women. Strong and confident women raise educated children, which leads to national progress. Empowering women is not only a matter of justice but also a step toward sustainable development. Therefore, women empowerment is essential for building a fair, strong, and prosperous world.</span></p><p><span> </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Marks Distribution:</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Highest Mark ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------09 Marks </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">(A) For Title (</span><span class=\"english\">Women Empowerment</span><span class=\"english\">) </span><span class=\"english\">-------------------------------------------------------------------</span><span class=\"english\">01</span><span> </span><span class=\"english\">Mark</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">(B) Topic Sentence (Introduction)</span><span class=\"english\"> -------------------------------------------------------------------------</span><span class=\"english\">01 Mark</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Women empowerment is the pursuit of equal rights, opportunities, and freedom for women in all aspects of life.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">(C) Context Explanation (</span><span class=\"english\">Empowering Women for Sustainable Development</span><span class=\"english\">)</span><span class=\"english\"> (Any 6) ----06 Marks</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">• Ensuring women's access to education, healthcare, and employment without discrimination.</span><span class=\"english\"><br/>‎• Boosting women's confidence to make choices and resist injustice.</span><span class=\"english\"><br/>‎• Breaking the cycle of poverty and ignorance through education.</span><span class=\"english\"><br/>‎• Promoting economic independence for women to support themselves and contribute to family income.</span><span class=\"english\"><br/>‎• Active participation in politics and leadership for balanced and democratic society.</span><span class=\"english\"><br/>‎• Improving health, reducing violence, and promoting gender equality.</span><span class=\"english\"><br/>‎• Raising educated children for national progress.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">(D) Conclusion --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------01 Mark </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Women's empowerment is crucial for creating a fair, robust, and prosperous global community.</span></p><p><span> </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Instructions:</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">1. </span><span class=\"english\">For every 3 spelling/grammatical mistakes, 01 mark has to be deducted.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">2</span><span class=\"english\">. We will consider up to 12 sentences. However, if a student writes more than 12 sentences but less than double (20 sentences), 50% of the deserving marks must be deducted. If it becomes double (20 sentences), full marks have to be deducted. </span><span class=\"english\">Comment: Write within 10 sentences.</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">3. </span><span class=\"english\">Students must write within a para. If a student writes more than one para, half of the deserving marks must be deducted. </span><span class=\"english\">(Comment: Write within single/one para).</span><span> </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">4.</span><span class=\"english\"> For writing only the title of the paragraph bears no mark.</span></p>"
