        "question_html": "<p><span class=\"english\">Explain the proverb:</span><span> </span><span class=\"english\">“Fortune </span><span class=\"english\">favours</span><span class=\"english\"> the brave” </span><span><span> </span></span><span class=\"english\"><span> </span>                                                       5</span></p>",
        "options_html": [],
        "correct_answer_html": null,
        "solution_html": "<p><span class=\"english\">The proverb \"Fortune </span><span class=\"english\">favours</span><span class=\"english\"> the brave\" means that people who are courageous and willing to take risks often receive good luck and success. Being brave means facing challenges and difficulties without fear. When someone is bold and tries new things, even if there is danger or uncertainty, they have a better chance of achieving their goals. This saying encourages us to be confident and take action instead of being afraid to try. It </span><span class=\"english\">reminds us that good opportunities often come to those who are willing to be brave and take chances.</span></p><p><span> </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Marks Distribution:</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Highest</span><span> </span><span class=\"english\">Mark</span><span class=\"english\">------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------</span><span class=\"english\">05 Marks</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">(A) Theme Of the Proverb </span><span class=\"english\">--------------------------------------------------------------------------</span><span class=\"english\">01 Mark</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">People who are courageous and willing to take risks often receive good luck and success. </span></p><p><span class=\"english\"> (B) Context Explanation </span><span class=\"english\">(</span><span class=\"english\">Any</span><span> </span><span class=\"english\">4 Points</span><span class=\"english\">) ---------------------------------------------------------</span><span class=\"english\">04 Marks</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">• Encourages bravery and risk-taking.</span><span class=\"english\"><br/>‎• Enhances chances of achieving goals.</span><span class=\"english\"><br/>‎• Encourages confidence and action.</span><span class=\"english\"><br/>‎• Emphasizes the importance of taking chances.</span><span class=\"english\"><br/>‎• Highlights that good opportunities often come to brave individuals.</span></p><p><span> </span></p><p><span class=\"english\">Instructions:</span></p><p><span class=\"english\">*For every 03 spelling or grammatical errors, 01 mark has to be deducted. However, mistakes regarding capital and small letters can be overlooked.</span><span> </span><span> </span></p>"
